</head>
<body>

{% include "header.njk" %}

  <section class="em-pagehead em-pagehead--band em-pagehead--plain">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="em-breadcrumb"><a href="index.html">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><span>Safeguarding</span></div>
      <h1><em>Safeguarding</em></h1>
      <p class="deck">The care of children and vulnerable adults is everyone's responsibility — and we take it very seriously at Emmanuel.</p>

    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="em-intro">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="em-body">
        <p class="em-lead">At Emmanuel we take safeguarding and the care of children and vulnerable people very seriously.</p>
        <p>Safeguarding is the responsibility of the whole church community. If you have any concern about the safety or wellbeing of a child or adult, please do not hesitate to speak to our Parish Safeguarding Officer or a member of the clergy.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="em-aside">
        <div class="em-aside-card">
          <h4>Parish Safeguarding Officer</h4>
          <p class="big" style="font-size:24px">Sarah Watts</p>
          <p>For any safeguarding concern or question, Sarah can be reached directly by email.</p>
          <a href="mailto:safeguarding@emmanuelnw6.com" class="em-btn em-btn--primary" style="margin-top:4px">safeguarding@emmanuelnw6.com</a>
        </div>
        <div class="em-placeholder">
          <p>Link to the parish safeguarding policy to follow.</p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="em-section em-section--band">
    <div class="inner inner--narrow">
      <div class="em-sectionhead" style="margin-bottom:32px">
        <div class="em-ornament is-leading">In an emergency</div>
        <h2 style="font-size:32px">If someone is in immediate danger</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="em-body">
        <p>If a child or adult is in immediate danger, always call the emergency services on <strong>999</strong>. You can also contact the Diocese of London safeguarding team, or the NSPCC and other national helplines, for confidential advice at any time.</p>
        <div class="em-placeholder" style="margin-top:8px"><p>Diocesan safeguarding contact details and national helpline numbers to be confirmed with the Parish Safeguarding Officer.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="em-callout">
    <div class="inner">
      <div><h3>Everyone is <em>responsible</em>.</h3><p>If something doesn't feel right, please speak up. Our Parish Safeguarding Officer is here to listen and to help.</p></div>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:14px;flex-wrap:wrap"><a href="mailto:safeguarding@emmanuelnw6.com" class="em-btn em-btn--tan">Email Sarah Watts</a><a href="contact.html" class="em-btn em-btn--ghost-light">Contact the clergy</a></div>
    </div>
  </section>

